### 4.4 webSearch

**Purpose**: Search the web using Exa Search for current information, facts, news, or external sources.

**Input Parameters**:
```json
{
  "query": "latest RERA amendments Maharashtra 2024",
  "topK": 5,
  "title": "Searching for RERA updates"
}
```

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| query | string | Yes | Search query (max 300 chars) |
| topK | integer | No | Results count (1-10, default: 5) |
| title | string | No | Progress title shown to user |

**Output**:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "query": "latest RERA amendments Maharashtra 2024",
  "results": [
    {
      "title": "Maharashtra RERA Amendment 2024",
      "url": "https://example.com/article",
      "snippet": "The Maharashtra government has amended...",
      "source": "example.com",
      "score": 0.95
    }
  ],
  "count": 5
}
```

**When to Use**:
- Need current information or news
- Researching external legal developments
- Finding recent case law or amendments
- User asks about current events

**When NOT to Use**:
- Searching personal documents (use searchDocuments)
- Searching workspace documents (use workspaceRagRetrieve)
- Need full page content (follow up with httpGet)

**Failure Modes**:
- API unavailable or rate limited
- No results for niche queries
- Results may be outdated or irrelevant
- Network timeouts

