### 4.5 httpGet

**Purpose**: Fetch a specific URL and convert it to readable markdown. Use after webSearch when page contents are needed.

**Input Parameters**:
```json
{
  "url": "https://example.com/legal-article",
  "title": "Reading legal article"
}
```

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| url | string | Yes | Fully qualified URL to fetch |
| title | string | No | Progress title shown to user |

**Output**:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "status": 200,
  "url": "https://example.com/legal-article",
  "mediaType": "text/markdown",
  "contentPreview": "# Article Title\n\nFull article content...",
  "bytesRead": 15000,
  "truncated": false
}
```

**When to Use**:
- Need full content from a specific URL
- Following up on webSearch results
- Reading online legal documents or articles

**When NOT to Use**:
- Searching for URLs (use webSearch first)
- Accessing private/internal URLs (blocked for security)
- Accessing localhost or private IPs (blocked)

**Failure Modes**:
- Invalid or unreachable URL
- Private/local URLs blocked
- Page requires authentication
- Content too large (truncated at 6,000 chars)
- Network timeouts

