## 5. Document Tools - Working with Documents

Document tools help the AI read, create, edit, and compare documents. These are the workhorses of document management.

### 5.1 readDocument

**Purpose**: Read the full text content of a document. Supports DOCX, PDF, images, and other formats.

**Input Parameters**:
```json
{
  "doc_id": "doc-123",
  "title": "Reading contract document"
}
```

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| doc_id | string | Yes | Document ID to read |
| title | string | No | Progress title shown to user |

**Output**:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "doc_id": "doc-123",
  "filename": "Contract_v2.docx",
  "content": "Full document text...",
  "file_type": "docx"
}
```

**When to Use**:
- Need to read a specific document's content
- Analyzing or reviewing a document
- Preparing for other operations (comparison, analysis)

**When NOT to Use**:
- Searching for documents (use searchDocuments)
- Reading workspace files (use workspaceRagRetrieve)
- Reading only specific sections (use findInDocument)

**Failure Modes**:
- Document not found
- Unsupported file format
- Document too large (truncated at 120,000 chars)
- Permission denied
- Corrupted file

---

### 5.2 findInDocument

**Purpose**: Search within a specific document for particular terms or sections. More efficient than reading the entire document.

**Input Parameters**:
```json
{
  "doc_id": "doc-123",
  "query": "termination clause",
  "title": "Finding termination clause"
}
```

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| doc_id | string | Yes | Document ID to search |
| query | string | Yes | Search term or phrase |
| title | string | No | Progress title shown to user |

**Output**:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "doc_id": "doc-123",
  "matches": [
    {
      "text": "This Agreement may be terminated by...",
      "position": 1520,
      "context": "...preceding text [MATCH] following text..."
    }
  ],
  "match_count": 3
}
```

**When to Use**:
- Looking for specific clauses in a document
- Need to locate sections quickly
- Follow-up after searchDocuments

**When NOT to Use**:
- Need full document content (use readDocument)
- Searching across multiple documents (use searchDocuments)

**Failure Modes**:
- Document not found
- No matches for query
- Query too vague

